00:00:01.730 --> 00:00:05.670
This is another brain teaser
that deals with people trying

00:00:05.670 --> 00:00:08.240
to logically deduce what's
on their forehead.

00:00:08.240 --> 00:00:15.939
And it's called the Forehead
Number Game.

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:23.400
So what's going to happen is I
guess you could say the god of

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:24.760
brain teasers is going
to get three

00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:25.790
people in a room together.

00:00:25.790 --> 00:00:28.250
Once again, these three people
are perfect logicians.

00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:38.710
Which means they have infallible
powers of logic.

00:00:38.710 --> 00:00:41.750
And they know that the other
two people-- they're three

00:00:41.750 --> 00:00:45.190
people in total --are also all
perfect logicians and have

00:00:45.190 --> 00:00:47.740
infallible powers of logic.

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:48.910
We get them into the circle,
and we'll say

00:00:48.910 --> 00:00:49.790
this is the top view.

00:00:49.790 --> 00:00:52.630
So this is the top of
one guy's forehead.

00:00:52.630 --> 00:00:54.410
They're all bald for
convenience.

00:00:54.410 --> 00:00:56.910
To make it easy to paint
things on their head.

00:00:56.910 --> 00:00:58.780
This time we're not going
to paint blue

00:00:58.780 --> 00:01:00.700
paint on their forehead.

00:01:00.700 --> 00:01:02.790
We're actually going
to paint numbers.

00:01:02.790 --> 00:01:07.040
So you could say the dungeon
master of this game, or the

00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:10.510
the god of this game says I'm
going to pick three numbers.

00:01:10.510 --> 00:01:13.830
So three numbers
will be picked.

00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:15.560
They will be unique.

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:19.260
Which means that no two of these
numbers are going to be

00:01:19.260 --> 00:01:19.880
the same number.

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:22.030
There are going to be three
different numbers.

00:01:22.030 --> 00:01:25.210
They're all going to be
greater than zero.

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:28.840
And this is key: One of the
numbers is going to be the sum

00:01:28.840 --> 00:01:30.090
of the other two.

00:01:38.950 --> 00:01:40.740
And they tell this to all
of the logicians.

00:01:40.740 --> 00:01:44.390
So this is the method that they
use to pick the number.

00:01:44.390 --> 00:01:46.940
And they tell this to the three
parties right there.

00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.790
And what they do is they take
these three numbers.

00:01:48.790 --> 00:01:50.970
And they write them on
people's foreheads.

00:01:50.970 --> 00:01:54.260
So say the numbers
are a, b and c.

00:01:54.260 --> 00:02:00.670
And we know that a plus-- let me
scroll down a little bit b

00:02:00.670 --> 00:02:03.030
is equal to c.

00:02:03.030 --> 00:02:05.640
We know that a, b and
c are different.

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:08.490
And we know that a is
greater than zero.

00:02:08.490 --> 00:02:10.520
b is greater than zero.

00:02:10.520 --> 00:02:13.540
And c is also greater
than zero.

00:02:13.540 --> 00:02:15.160
What they do is they paint
them on their heads.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:17.790
So this guy will have
a on his forehead.

00:02:17.790 --> 00:02:19.820
This guy will have b
on his forehead.

00:02:19.820 --> 00:02:22.900
And let's say this guy has
c on his forehead.

00:02:22.900 --> 00:02:25.100
And so when this guy looks out--
and you know, the reason

00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:27.290
we're even putting things on
people's foreheads is because

00:02:27.290 --> 00:02:29.070
you can't see what's on
your own forehead.

00:02:29.070 --> 00:02:30.370
No tricks involved here.

00:02:30.370 --> 00:02:33.960
All you can see is what's on the
forehead of the other two

00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:35.100
